            "fact_text": "Formation & OriginsThe primary difference between mined and lab grown diamonds is the way they are formed, and how and when they originate. Mined, or natural diamonds are formed deep within the Earth over millions and billions of years. These diamonds are formed due to extreme natural pressure and heat conditions. They are then brought to the surface via tectonic and volcanic activity. These diamonds are then extracted using large mining operations. While this natural formation makes mined diamonds a rare occurrence, due to a lack of control, a lot of natural factors and inconsistencies contribute to impurities, inclusions, and tints. On the other hand, lab grown diamonds are created under highly controlled technologically advanced labs using techniques that replicate the exact natural environmental conditions that occur during the formation of the natural diamond, only more controlled. This enables the lab grown diamonds to be produced in weeks instead of millions and billions of years like mined diamonds. Thus, the origin of the diamond goes a long way in impacting its rarity, quality, and accessibility. Whether you prioritize ethical sourcing, sustainability, affordability, quality, or innovation, understanding the formation and origin of the diamond you’re purchasing is essential to make an informed decision."
